DESCRIPTION

	AMIGAphile is a non-profit organization dedicated to supporting the
Amiga computer.  The AMIGAphile newsletter is produced in order to keep
Amiga users informed.  The newsletter is composed of letters and articles
written by Amiga owners and users.
	The newsletter is distributed in a number of forms.  Each of these
forms is targeted at a specific type of user.  AMIGAphile's goal is to
get a copy of AMIGAphile into the hands of every Amiga owner and user.
Only as an organized group can Amiga users have an influence on software
and hardware manufactures.

Form             Distribution           Purpose
================ ====================== ==================================
ASCII text       Internet (email/ftp)   For viewing on screen
                 Private BBSs

troff formatted  Internet (email/ftp)   A more structured form useful
                                        for printing

postscript       Internet (email/ftp)   Nearly identical to the hardcopy
                                        form includes pictures.  File
                                        size tends to be 1.5 megs or more.

hardcopy         US postal service      Printed from postscript (along
                                        with any photographs) and mailed
                                        to those who do not have access
                                        by any other means.

	AMIGAphile's motto is "by the user, for the user".  This newsletter
is for you, the Amiga user.  If you have a questions, comments,
suggestions, or submission, write the author listed above.
	If you would like to be put on the AMIGAphile emailing list, please
send your email address along with the form you wish to receive to the
author listed above.

